en_139633_0	The Foreign Employment Bureau states that sending Sri Lankans for jobs in Saudi Arabia should be reviewed.
en_139633_1	Saudi Arabia is facing economic crisis after the prices of oil fell in the world market.
en_139633_2	Consequent to this situation, factories in the country seemed to be closing down gradually thereby denying employment to thousands of expatriates.
en_139633_3	Working Director of the Foreign Employment Bureau Upul Deshapriya said that there are unemployed Sri Lankans amongst those expatriates.
en_139633_4	Meanwhile Indian External Minister Sushma Swaraj told parliament that steps will be taken to see 10 thousand such dismissed workers be deported.
